<dl id="s16021ca"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us16" href="#s16021ca">Eumeus: </a><a href="../../FF/unbs/s16all.htm#s16021ca">sector 21(ca)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Eum. fosterson of Laertes, with Ctimene</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Then spake to him the swineherd <font color="green">[<mark>Eumaeus</mark>]</font>, a master of men: &lsquo;Yea now, stranger, I will plainly tell thee all. <mark>Laertes</mark> yet lives, and prays evermore to Zeus that his life may waste from out his limbs within his halls. For he has wondrous sorrow for his son that is far away, and for the wedded lady his wise wife, whose death afflicted him in chief and brought him to old age before his day. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> So long as she was on earth, though in much sorrow, I was glad to ask and enquire concerning her, for that <mark>she herself had reared me along with long-robed Ctimene</mark>, her noble daughter, the youngest of her children. <small> Butcher &amp; Lang, trans. <a name="OHBL2" href="/udra/udex.htm#OHBL2"><cite title="source">The Odyssey Of Homer</cite></a> (1906), 251</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
